Bundesbank’s Weber Earned More Than ECB’s Trichet Last Year

-- B y   C h r i s t i a n   V i t s   a n d   J e f f   B l a c k
-- 
2011-03-08T13:00:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-08/bundesbank-s-weber-earned-more-than-ecb-s-trichet-last-year.html
Bundesbank President  Axel Weber 
earned more than European Central Bank President  Jean-Claude Trichet  last year.  Weber, who sits on the ECB’s Governing Council, which is
chaired by Trichet, was paid 391,522 euros ($545,821) last year,
up 0.9 percent from 2009, the Frankfurt-based Bundesbank said in
its 2010 annual report today. Trichet’s pay rose 2 percent to
367,863 euros in 2010, the ECB said last week.  Federal Reserve Chairman  Ben S. Bernanke  earned $199,700
last year, while  Bank of England  Governor  Mervyn King  was paid
305,368 pounds ($494,085).  Bank of Japan  Governor Masaaki Shirakawa’s salary was 34.4 million yen ($417,171).  To contact the reporters on this story:
Christian Vits in Frankfurt at 
 cvits@bloomberg.net ;
Jeff Black in  Frankfurt  at 
 jblack25@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
